{
  "info": {
    "name": "Laravel Gateway API - Microservices Sample",
    "description": "Postman collection for the Laravel API Gateway. All requests go through the gateway at `localhost:8000` which proxies to the downstream Node.js microservices.\n\n## Authentication\n- `POST /api/auth/login` returns a JWT token + user object.\n- The collection variable `token` is **automatically set** by the Login request's test script.\n- Protected endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}`.\n\n## Architecture\n```\nBrowser/Frontend (:3000) → Laravel Gateway (:8000) → Microservices (:3001-:3003)\n```\n\n## Seed Credentials\n| Username | Password | Role |\n|----------|----------|------|\n| admin    | password | admin |\n| john     | password | user  |\n\n## Seed Products (IDs 1-5)\n1. Wireless Headphones ($79.99)\n2. Smart Watch ($199.99)\n3. Laptop Stand ($49.99)\n4. Mechanical Keyboard ($129.99)\n5. USB-C Hub ($34.99)\n\n## Seed Orders\n1. Admin's order (completed) - 1 item\n2. John's order (processing) - 2 items\n3. John's order (pending) - 1 item\n\nValid order statuses: `pending`, `processing`, `completed`, `cancelled`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has status and service fields', () => {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.service).to.eql('api-gateway');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.timestamp).to.exist;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Simple health check to confirm the gateway is running. No authentication required."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"service\": \"api-gateway\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2024-07-07T12:00:00Z\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', () => {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has token and user', () => {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.token).to.exist;",
                  "  pm.expect(json.user).to.exist;",
                  "  pm.expect(json.user.username).to.eql('admin');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.user.role).to.eql('admin');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.token);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"admin\",\n  \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate with username and password. Returns a JWT token (auto-saved to `{{token}}`) and user data.\n\nValid credentials:\n- `admin` / `password` (role: admin)\n- `john` / `password` (role: user)"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Success (admin)",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"token\": \"eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOjEsInVzZXJuYW1lIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJuYW1lIjoiQWRtaW4gVXNlciIsImVtYWlsIjoiYWRtaW5AZXhhbXBsZS5jb20iLCJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJpYXQiOjE3MjAzNzQyMDAsImV4cCI6MTcyMDQ2MDYwMH0.example\",\n  \"user\": {\n    \"id\": 1,\n    \"username\": \"admin\",\n    \"name\": \"Admin User\",\n    \"email\": \"admin@example.com\",\n    \"role\": \"admin\",\n    \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Invalid Credentials",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Invalid credentials\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 201', () => {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has user data without password', () => {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.id).to.exist;",
                  "  pm.expect(json.username).to.eql('jane');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.password).to.be.undefined;",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"jane\",\n  \"password\": \"secret123\",\n  \"name\": \"Jane Smith\",\n  \"email\": \"jane@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Create a new user account.\n\nValidation rules:\n- `username`: required, min 3 characters, must be unique\n- `password`: required, min 6 characters\n- `name`: required\n- `email`: required, valid email format\n\nNote: Does NOT return a JWT token. Call `/api/auth/login` after registering."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Created",
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": 3,\n  \"username\": \"jane\",\n  \"name\": \"Jane Smith\",\n  \"email\": \"jane@example.com\",\n  \"role\": \"user\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-07-07T12:00:00.000Z\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Validation Error",
              "status": "Unprocessable Entity",
              "code": 422,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"message\": \"The given data was invalid.\",\n  \"errors\": {\n    \"username\": [\"The username field is required.\"],\n    \"password\": [\"The password field is required.\"],\n    \"name\": [\"The name field is required.\"],\n    \"email\": [\"The email field is required.\"]\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "Duplicate Username",
              "status": "Conflict",
              "code": 409,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"error\": \"Username already exists\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
